Done. The kill-before-spawn logic:

1. Reads `spawn_pids.txt` and finds any existing entry matching the target nucleus
2. Kills the old process with `taskkill /F /PID <pid> /T` (tree-kill)
3. Removes the stale entry from the PID file (or deletes the file if empty)
4. Then proceeds with the normal spawn

